HEADWORD: Eclampsia
<hw>Ec*lamp"si*a</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[NL., from
Gr. <?/ a shining forth, fr. <?/ to shine forth; <?/ out + <?/ to
shine.]</ety> <fld>(Med.)</fld> <def>A fancied perception of flashes of
light, a symptom of epilepsy; hence, epilepsy itself;
convulsions.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><note>⟦hand⟧ The term is generally restricted to a convulsive
affection attending pregnancy and parturition, and to infantile
convulsions.</note>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

